n the read succeeds and the content is empty; otherwise log and skip backfill.\\n\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go:372\\nAuthor: Copilot\\nBody: `backfilledPrompt` is set even when writing `prompt.txt` fails, which can later update session state to a value that was never persisted to disk. Only set `backfilledPrompt` after a successful write (and/or gate the session-state backfill on the write succeeding).\\n\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go:374\\nAuthor: Copilot\\nBody: `ExtractPrompts` errors are silently dropped (`extractErr == nil` check). For parity with modified-file extraction (which logs warnings), consider logging a warn/debug when prompt extraction fails so missing prompts are diagnosable in the field.\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go:375\\nAuthor: Copilot\\nBody: Backfill happens before commit message generation, but the commit message still uses `LastPrompt` loaded from session state (which is empty in exec mode). Consider using `backfilledPrompt` as the source for `commitMessage` when `LastPrompt` is empty so the step commit message reflects the extracted prompt.\\n\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle_test.go:638\\nAuthor: Copilot\\nBody: This test ignores the return value from `handleLifecycleTurnStart`. If the handler returns an error after partially writing side effects, the test can still pass and hide regressions. Prefer asserting `require.NoError(t, err)` here.\\n\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle_test.go:684\\nAuthor: Copilot\\nBody: This test ignores the return value from `handleLifecycleTurnEnd`. Prefer `require.NoError` so failures in turn-end processing don’t get masked by later filesystem assertions.\\n\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go:376\\nAuthor: cursor[bot]\\nBody: ### Backfilled prompt not used for commit message generation\\n\\n**Medium Severity**\\n\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION START -->\\nThe `backfilledPrompt` is successfully extracted from the transcript before commit message generation, but `generateCommitMessage` reads `lastPrompt` from session state's `LastPrompt`, which is still empty at that point (hooks never fired). The `backfilledPrompt` value is only written to session state after `SaveStep`. This means the checkpoint commit for the current turn always gets a generic fallback message like \\\"Factory AI Droid session updates\\\" instead of using the extracted prompt, defeating a key benefit of the backfill.\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION END -->\\n\\n<!-- BUGBOT_BUG_ID: 51444018-fc96-409d-be25-6c61cc2a13a4 -->\\n\\n<!-- LOCATIONS START\\ncmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go#L406-L411\\ncmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go#L357-L375\\ncmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go#L519-L531\\nLOCATIONS END -->\\n<details>\\n<summary>Additional Locations (2)</summary>\\n\\n- [`cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go#L357-L375`](https://github.com/entireio/cli/blob/8fa1853f1865df5230cad5b69f492ca1d73a029c/cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go#L357-L375)\\n- [`cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go#L519-L531`](https://github.com/entireio/cli/blob/8fa1853f1865df5230cad5b69f492ca1d73a029c/cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go#L519-L531)\\n\\n</details>\\n\\n<div><a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/open?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Cursor\\\" width=\\\"115\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"></picture></a>&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/agents?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Web\\\" width=\\\"99\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"></picture></a></div>\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go:520\\nAuthor: cursor[bot]\\nBody: ### Early return skips session state prompt backfill update\\n\\n**Low Severity**\\n\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION START -->\\nWhen no files are modified (`totalChanges == 0`), the early return at line 471 skips the session state `LastPrompt` backfill at lines 523–531. If the prompt was successfully extracted and `backfilledPrompt` is non-empty, the `prompt.txt` file is written but `state.LastPrompt` is never updated. This means `entire status` (which reads `LastPrompt` to display the session prompt) shows an empty prompt, and subsequent turns won't have the prior prompt in session state.\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION END -->\\n\\n<!-- BUGBOT_BUG_ID: ref1_d08a696c-bf8a-4d09-af1f-27e307fcfbbc -->\\n\\n<!-- LOCATIONS START\\ncmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go#L463-L471\\ncmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go#L519-L531\\nLOCATIONS END -->\\n<details>\\n<summary>Additional Locations (1)</summary>\\n\\n- [`cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go#L519-L531`](https://github.com/entireio/cli/blob/8fa1853f1865df5230cad5b69f492ca1d73a029c/cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go#L519-L531)\\n\\n</details>\\n\\n<div><a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/open?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Cursor\\\" width=\\\"115\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"></picture></a>&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/agents?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/f